#
# Standpoint-poset data for the purrdf:heldIn EXTEND case. The claim `ex:claim`
# reifies `<< ex:earth ex:shape ex:sphere >>` from the vantage of the sharper
# frame `ex:geodesy`, which DIRECTLY sharpens (is more specific than) the broader
# frame `ex:commonSense` (the materialized poset edge the engine reads — it does
# NOT compute transitive closure). So a claim held in `ex:geodesy` counts as held
# in `ex:commonSense`. No incumbent SPARQL engine can express this poset-aware
# "held-in-a-broader-frame" relation.
@prefix ex:     <http://ex/> .
@prefix rdf:    <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix purrdf:  <https://blackcatinformatics.ca/purrdf/> .

ex:claim rdf:reifies <<( ex:earth ex:shape ex:sphere )>> ;
         purrdf:accordingTo ex:geodesy .

ex:geodesy purrdf:sharpens ex:commonSense .
